	<div class="container">
		<div class="project-hero__content">
			
			<h1 class="project-hero__title">Overlooked mental health &#8220;catastrophe:&#8221; Vanishing board-and-care-homes leave residents with few options</h1>

			
						<p class="project-hero__intro">Housing costs have forced many board-and-care homes to shutter. Mental health advocates say the closures will exacerbate the homeless crisis in California.</p>
			
							<div class="project-hero__caption">

											<svg role="img" class="icon icon--camera" aria-label="camera"><use xlink:href="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/themes/thenewsproject/dist/svg/dist/symbol/svg/sprite.symbol.svg#camera"></use></svg>						<span>Resident Concepcion Wedell makes her way to the kitchen while walking past Setsuko Letchford in the living room at Palarca&#039;s Rest Home in San Francisco. Photos by Jessica Christian, San Francisco Chronicle</span>
									</div>
					</div>
	</div>
</div>

